
  <sn><md>### Summary

| **Stage**                    | **Location**                      | **Oxygen Requirement** | **Key Processes / Products**                                                |
| ---------------------------- | --------------------------------- | ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Glycolysis**               | Cytoplasm                         | With or without oxygen | Glucose (6C) → 2 Pyruvates (3C); produces small amount of ATP and NADH      |
| **TCA Cycle (Krebs Cycle)**  | Mitochondrial matrix              | Only with oxygen       | Pyruvate → Acetyl Co-A → CO₂; generates NADH and FADH₂, some ATP            |
| **Electron Transport Chain** | Mitochondrial membranes (cristae) | Only with oxygen       | Transfers electrons from NADH &amp; FADH₂ to O₂ → H₂O; produces majority of ATP |
</md></sn>
